chemaxon.marvin.modules
Interface MoleculeIterators.AtomIteratorInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
MacroMolecule.Polymer.AtomIterator, MoleculeIterators.MoleculeAtomIterator
Enclosing interface:
MoleculeIterators
public static interface MoleculeIterators.AtomIteratorInterface

Classes that implement the AtomIteratorInterface interface enumerate atoms of a molecule. Such molecule is not exclusively the instance of the Molecule, as for instance components of a MacroMolecule object can also be considered as molecules.
An atom iterator that implements this interface does not neccesarily lists all atoms of the molecule but a subset specified by further methods provided by the particular atom iterator though not required by this interface (e.g. alpha carbon atoms of a protein chain).
